fields.name: Gamemaster

fields.name: Combatant Commander
fields.description: Chooses how to divide supply points amongst the three branch commanders.

fields.description: Responds to political scenarios, and can gain or lose supply points for their team based on their performance.

fields.name: Air Force Chief of Staff

fields.name: Air Force Operations Commander

fields.name: Air Force Operations Vice Commander
fields.description: Controls non-logistic Air Force units' movements, and can do actions using supply points allocated by the Air Force Chief of Staff. Unlike Air Force Operations Commanders, this role cannot directly message the Air Force Chief of staff.

fields.name: Air Force Logistics Commander
fields.description: Controls logistic Air Force units' movements, and generates supply points at supply nodes, which can be moved along a  'chain' of logistic units.

fields.name: City
fields.description:
A population center worth the highest amounts of victory points. 
To capture, any ground unit must move through a tile using its own movement, and not via a logistic unit.

fields.name: Port
fields.description:
A city with a port terminal. If a Sealift Command Ship Group (SCSG) is docked (adjacent) to it, then it can act as a Supply Node.
To capture, any ground unit must move through a tile using its own movement, and not via a logistic unit.

fields.name: Ground Base
fields.description:
A strategically significant landmark where ground units may restore their health once captured.
To capture, any ground unit must move through a tile using its own movement, and not via a logistic unit.

fields.name: Airfield
fields.description:
A landmark with significant air facilities.
To capture, any ground unit must move through a tile using its own movement, and not via a logistic unit.

fields.name: Supply Node
fields.description:
An industrial center where supply points are generated.
To capture, any ground unit must move through a tile using its own movement, and not via a logistic unit.

fields.name: Stockpile
fields.description:
Created when a Logistic Group unit deposits supplies on the ground. Any number of supplies can be stored in this landmark.
Stockpiles can be depleted by adjacent units taking supplies, destroyed by an attack, or captured through occupation. The health of the stockpile is equal to the number of supplies * 5. 
To capture, any ground unit must move through a tile using its own movement, and not via a logistic unit.
